 Review comment:
   I will admit to not being particularly principled in this selection.  I don't think this is solely about SIMD.  Having a fixed size loop allows for unrolling which even without SIMD avoids branches.  I tried changing this just to the size of AVX registers on my box and saw a small slowdown on the BitVectorHelper tests, this could have been noise.  I don't believe unrolling was happening here before because based on my reading it seems that stride lengths of 8 are not considered for unrolling.

